SIMPLE: adrift
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adrift
<hw>A*drift"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv. & a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>a-</ets> (for <ets>on</ets>) + <ets>drift</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Floating at random; in a drifting condition; at the mercy of wind
and waves. Also fig.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So on the sea shall be set <qex>adrift</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Were from their daily labor turned <qex>adrift</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adrip</ent>⟦br⟧
